Third-Party Data and API Notice (제3자 데이터 및 API 고지)

The Software utilizes and processes data and services from the following third-party sources, which are governed by their respective licenses and terms of service:

A. Word Existence Data (단어 존재 여부 데이터)
* Source: National Institute of Korean Language (국립국어원) - Standard Korean Dictionary Open API
* License: Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 2.0 Korea (CC BY-SA 2.0 KR)
* Obligation: Any derived work utilizing this data must maintain the same CC BY-SA 2.0 KR license.
* Attribution: All publicly displayed usages derived from this data are attributed to the National Institute of Korean Language, as required by the license.

B. Morphological Analysis and Correction API (형태소 분석 및 교정 API)
* Source: Baikal AI Inc. (주식회사 바이칼에이아이) - Bareun Morphological Analyzer and Corrector
* Terms of Use: Governed by the separate Terms of Service between the Software owner and Baikal AI Inc.
* User Content Notice (Terms Article 9): By using this Software, the user agrees that the input text (Content) may be transmitted to and processed by Baikal AI Inc. for the purpose of service provision and feature improvement.
* Restriction: The Software's usage of this API is strictly limited to the agreed-upon license scope (e.g., usage limits, non-creation of secondary works).

C. English Dictionary Data (영문 사전 데이터)
* Source: Merriam-Webster Dictionary API
* Terms of Service: https://dictionaryapi.com/info/terms-of-service
* Restriction & Obligation: All usage of the Merriam-Webster API is subject to their Terms of Service, which generally requires **non-commercial use** and adherence to specific **daily query limits**.
* Disclaimer: This Source Code License (MIT) does not supersede or modify the usage terms for the Merriam-Webster API. Users are responsible for ensuring their usage complies with all Merriam-Webster terms.